Description: Fragment of North Ionian pottery krater? Interior reserved; exterior: above glazed streakily with incised scale pattern in double outline with red dots at centre; below, two bands and broad reserved area.
Curator's comments: From same vase as Boston MFA 1888.1088.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1154)
